{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17620078","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17620078"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:39:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:39:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16604"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16604","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16604"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.66,0,0.06,0.29,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9295"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75897"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9295","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9295"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16604"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61410"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"43"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1315"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5304"},{"type":"tags","id":"5309"},{"type":"tags","id":"8503"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22010"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22185"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75897","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75897"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe levonorgestrel-releasing intrauterine system (Mirena) is a long-acting reversible contraceptive device that releases a synthetic progestogen directly into the uterine cavity.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary mechanism of action of the levonorgestrel-releasing intrauterine system?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Causes endometrial atrophy and cervical mucus thickening","Blocks fallopian tubes through fibrosis","Disrupts corpus luteum formation","Prevents ovulation by suppressing follicle-stimulating hormone","Triggers an inflammatory response that destroys sperm"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary mechanism of action of Mirena is \u003Cstrong\u003Eendometrial atrophy and cervical mucus thickening\u003C/strong\u003E caused by local levonorgestrel release. The progestogen effect causes creation of an environment hostile to sperm transport and implantation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA small amount of systemic absorption of levonorgestrel occurs, however the amount is insufficient to \u003Cstrong\u003Eprevent ovulation via suppression of follicle-stimulating hormone.\u003C/strong\u003E Ovulation may be suppressed by local effects, but this is not the primary mechanism of Mirena.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETriggering an inflammatory response that destroys sperm\u003C/strong\u003E is the mechanism of action of copper intrauterine devices, not hormonal ones.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe device does not \u003Cstrong\u003Eblock fallopian tubes through fibrosis\u003C/strong\u003E as it does not cause structural or changes to the fallopian tubes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile progestogens can affect ovarian function, \u003Cstrong\u003Edisruption of corpus luteum formation\u003C/strong\u003E is not the primary mechanism of action of the intrauterine system.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe local delivery system allows for lower total hormone doses while maintaining high endometrial concentrations, resulting in fewer systemic side effects compared to oral contraceptives.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The levonorgestrel-releasing intrauterine system (Mirena) primarily works by causing endometrial atrophy and cervical mucus thickening.","Levonorgestrel is a synthetic progestogen that provides effective contraception for up to 8 years when delivered via an intrauterine system.","Local delivery of levonorgestrel results in minimal systemic effects while maintaining high endometrial concentrations."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Kailasam C, Cahill D. Review of the safety, efficacy and patient acceptability of the levonorgestrel-releasing intrauterine system. Patient Prefer Adherence. 2008;2:293-302. Published 2008 Feb 2. doi:10.2147/ppa.s3464","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61410"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16604"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61410","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61410"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-01T12:44:43+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T12:45:16+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9295"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75897"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"43","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/43"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc8a","name":"Ph